.TH "batadv_frag_create" 9 "batadv_frag_create" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_frag_create \- create a fragment from skb
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct sk_buff *" batadv_frag_create
.BI "(struct net_device *net_dev "  ","
.BI "struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "struct batadv_frag_packet *frag_head "  ","
.BI "unsigned int fragment_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "net_dev" 12
outgoing device for fragment
.IP "skb" 12
skb to create fragment from
.IP "frag_head" 12
header to use in new fragment
.IP "fragment_size" 12
size of new fragment
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Split the passed skb into two fragments: A new one with size matching the
passed mtu and the old one with the rest. The new skb contains data from the
tail of the old skb.
.SH "RETURN"
the new fragment, NULL on error.
